.TH hp6038 1 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
hp6038 \- control HP 603xA power supplies
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B hp6038 [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBhp6038\fR controls the HP/Agilent 603xA power supply via its 
GPIB interface.
\fBhp6038\fR performs actions in the order they appear on the command line.
.SH OPTIONS
\fBhp6038\fR accepts the following command line options:
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-name\fR name
Set the name used to look up the instrument address in
the config file.  The default is \fIhp6038\fR.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-address\fR address
Set the instrument address.
See gpib-utils.conf(5) for a description of address formats.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-clear\fR
Clear the instrument to its power-on state, disables its output,
and clears any foldback condition.
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-local\fR
Enable the front panel.
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-get-idn\fR 
Print instrument model.
.TP
\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-\-selftest\fR 
Run instrument selftest.
.TP
\fB\-I\fR, \fB\-\-iset\fR float
Set current in amps.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-vset\fR float
Set voltage in volts.
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-out\fR 0|1
Enable/disable output.
.TP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-foldback\fR off|cv|cc
Enables or disables foldback protection which will disable power supply 
output if power supply switches to whatever mode, CV or CC, is defined
as the fold (error) condition [Default off].
Use the \fB\-\-clear\fR option to clear a foldback condition.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-samples\fR number
Select number of current and voltage samples to take [Default 0].
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-period\fR period
Set sample period [Default 0s].
.SH FILES
@X_SYSCONFDIR@/gpib-utils.conf
.br
~/.gpib-utils.conf
.SH "SEE ALSO"
gpib-utils.conf(5)
